# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# prompt-autotuner — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values.
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# All options here can also be set in ~/.autotuner/config.yaml.
# Priority: .env (process.env) → ~/.autotuner/config.yaml → defaults
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# [REQUIRED] OpenRouter API key — used by the Express server to proxy LLM calls.
# Get one at https://openrouter.ai
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# [OPTIONAL] Express API server port (default: 3001) — Vite port is hardcoded in vite.config.ts
# PORT=3001

# [OPTIONAL] CLI only — used by bin/autotuner.js to set Express port at startup
# API_PORT=3001

# [OPTIONAL] Saved prompts storage backend (default: file)
#   file         — ~/.autotuner/saved-prompts.json (recommended)
#   localstorage — browser localStorage only
# STORAGE_BACKEND=file
